    <td class="yahooinn" bgcolor="#ffffff" align="left" valign="top" style="font-family: 'Century Gothic', sans-serif, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;; color:#000000; text-align:left; font-size:16px; line-height:23px;padding:0 20px; margin:0; color:#000000;">Dear {!IF(Contact.Parent_Name__c<>"",""&(Contact.Parent_Name__c)&"","Parent or Guardian")},
<br><br>
NCS is just around the corner! To prepare, <b>please read this pack carefully</b>. There’s lots of important information here, including:
<ul><li><b>Your NCS Timetable</b> – shows meeting points, dates, times and accommodation for the residential parts. You will need to organise {!Contact.FirstName}’s transport to the meeting points and from the return points. <b><a href ="{!Wave__c.Programme_Pack_Letters__c}"target="_blank">Click here</b></a>.
<li><b>Your NCS Information Booklet</b> – gives you essential information about NCS, including packing lists and how to contact us in an emergency. </b><b><a href ="{!Wave__c.Programme_booklet__c}"target="_blank">Click here</b></a>.</li></ul> 
As {!Contact.FirstName}’s parent or guardian, there are two important things you need to do before {!Contact.FirstName} starts NCS:
<ol type="1"><li>{!IF(Contact.Parent_Emergency_Phone__c = "","<B>Please contact us to give us an emergency phone number for you. We do not have one and we need this before NCS starts.</b><BR>","<b>Please check we have the correct emergency phone number for you. The number we have is:<center> "& ( Contact.Parent_Emergency_Phone__c ) &". </center></b> Please contact us if you need to change this.")} It’s your responsibility to make sure we have a correct number and someone will be available to take calls on it.<br><br>
<li><b>Please contact us if there have been any changes to the medical, support or dietary information you gave us about {!Contact.FirstName}, or if you need to give us any other details.</b><br>
You’re responsible for making sure we have full and up-to-date medical, support and dietary information, including details of any medication.<sup><b>1</b></sup></li></ol>
You can call us on <b>0203 542 2400</b> or email us at <b><a href ="mailto:contact@ncsthechallenge.org "target="_blank">contact@ncsthechallenge.org</b></a> if you have any questions or need to give us any information. Please quote {!Contact.FirstName}’s NCS ID number: <b>{!Contact.NCS_ID__c}</b>.
{!IF(Wave_Selection__c.All_girl_wave__c = "Yes","<br><br><B>Please note: </b>All young people and pastoral support staff on this programme will be female. However, there may be some male staff, or male young people from other groups, at the venues.","")}</left>
<br><br>
If  {!Contact.FirstName} can no longer attend NCS, please contact us so we can offer their place to another young person. 
<br><br>
We’re really looking forward to welcoming  {!Contact.FirstName} to NCS!
<br><br>
The NCS Team - The Challenge<BR><BR><HR><sup><b><small>1</small></b></sup> <small>As standard, The Challenge does not accept responsibility for any medication that a young person brings on NCS. This includes administering medication. Please see our consent statement for more information. If there needs to be an exception for the young person or if you have any concerns, please contact us.</small>
